# IoT ESP32 FreeRTOS Project

This project is an ESP32-based IoT application using PlatformIO and FreeRTOS. It is designed for modular task management, including uptime tracking, button input, and light control. The codebase is structured for clarity, maintainability, and easy extension.

PlatformIO streamlines the setup of the ESP32 development environment, making it efficient and accessible for rapid prototyping and deployment.

## Features

- Modular FreeRTOS tasks for uptime, button, and light control
- Clean separation of application logic and hardware abstraction
- Easy integration of new features via the `lib/` directory
- Example plans and deprecated code for reference

## Directory Structure

| Directory/File  | Description                                              |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| .github/        | GitHub configuration files                               |
| .gitignore      | Git ignore rules                                         |
| .pio/           | PlatformIO build files                                   |
| .vscode/        | VS Code configuration                                    |
| graveyard/      | Deprecated code for reference                            |
| include/        | Project header files                                     |
| lib/            | Project-specific libraries (uptime, button, light, etc.) |
| plan.excalidraw | Project plan (Excalidraw format)                         |
| platformio.ini  | PlatformIO configuration                                 |
| README          | Project documentation (this file)                        |
| sdkconfig       | ESP32 SDK configuration                                  |
| src/            | Main application source code                             |
| test/           | PlatformIO Test Runner and tests                         |

## Build & Upload Instructions

1. Install [PlatformIO](https://platformio.org/) and [VS Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/).
2. Open the project folder in VS Code.
3. Use PlatformIO commands to build and upload firmware to your ESP32 device:
   - Build: `PlatformIO: Build`
   - Upload: `PlatformIO: Upload`

